(Place this as demo/run_demo.sh; make executable: chmod +x run_demo.sh)
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -e
cd "$(dirname "$0")"
python3 server.py

Dockerfile
(Place this as demo/Dockerfile — serves static files with nginx)
FROM nginx:stable-alpine
COPY . /usr/share/nginx/html
EXPOSE 80
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

README.txt
(Place this as demo/README.txt)
Quick demo
- Local (fast): python3 server.py  # opens browser automatically
- Docker: docker build -t demo . && docker run -p 8080:80 demo
- To stop: CTRL+C (local) or docker stop <id>

Packaging & auto-launch options (short)
- macOS: create a small .app wrapper or use platypus to run server.py at startup; add Chrome launch flags --app, --kiosk for kiosk mode.
- Windows: Generate an exe with pyinstaller for server and create a simple start shortcut; use chrome --app or set up kiosk via assigned access.
- Linux: use systemd user service to run server on login and open a browser in kiosk mode; example unit file can be provided.
- Docker: easiest to run in cloud or client machine without Python.
- Electron: wrap the SPA if you need a desktop app with deeper OS integration.

Notes for demos to clients
- Auto-play should be togglable (we included play/pause and keyboard controls).
- Prepare canned datasets for different personas — simply add more objects in features array.
- If you want to record or demo scripted user interactions (video-style tours), incorporate a script runner that triggers UI events in sequence; I can add a JSON-based script runner.
- If you want server-driven live data or multi-user collaboration simulation, add a tiny websocket server (Flask-SocketIO or node) and a simulated client that streams events.

Next steps I can do for you
- Create the files in a git branch (I can add them to the repo here).
- Add a systemd unit, macOS .plist, or Windows shortcut/autostart template for kiosk deployments.
- Add a scripted tour engine (JSON-driven) that steps through features and highlights buttons and clicks.
- Package into a Docker Compose or single-file distributable.

